## S 3. Search Page Extraction

**Called once per query** (see HEARTBEAT.md §4 for multi-query loop).
Navigate to `https://www.threads.com/search?q={QUERY}&serp_type=default&filter=recent`, then extract with 3s embedded wait.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://www.threads.com/search?q={QUERY}&serp_type=default&filter=recent"}' 2>&1
```

Returns enriched posts with `bio`, `ageHours` fields. `postId` extracted from URL — use directly for grep pre-check.

**Filters applied inline:**
- Skips `/media` URL variants (duplicate links from image posts)
- Skips posts with noise keywords: hiring, job seekers, apply now, dm me for, check my link, onlyfans, follow back
- Skips posts with < 30 chars of real text (link spam / emoji only)
- Skips posts with 0 likes AND 0 replies (zero engagement — not worth commenting)
- Skips posts older than 4h with 0 likes (nobody cared)

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const posts = []; const links = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a[href*=\"/post/\"]')); const seen = new Set(); const noiseKw = ['hiring', 'job seekers', 'apply now', 'dm me for', 'check my link', 'onlyfans', 'follow back', 'beacons.ai', 'linktr.ee', 'linktree', 'youtube channel', 'subscribe', 'join my', 'check out my', 'i feature', 'sign up']; links.forEach(link => { if (link.href.includes('/media')) return; if (seen.has(link.href) || posts.length >= 10) return; seen.add(link.href); let container = link; for (let i = 0; i < 9; i++) { container = container.parentElement; if (!container) return; } const author = link.href.split('/')[3].replace('@', ''); const postId = link.href.match(/\\/post\\/([^/?]+)/)?.[1] || ''; const lines = container.innerText.split(String.fromCharCode(10)).filter(l => l.trim()); const tsPattern = /^\\d+[smhdw]$|^\\d+\\/\\d+\\/\\d+$/; let bio = '', timeStr = '', contentStart = 1; if (lines[1] && !tsPattern.test(lines[1])) { bio = lines[1]; timeStr = lines[2] || ''; contentStart = 3; } else { timeStr = lines[1] || ''; contentStart = 2; } let ageHours = 0; const tsMatch = timeStr.match(/^(\\d+)([smhdw])$/); if (tsMatch) { const n = parseInt(tsMatch[1]), u = tsMatch[2]; if (u === 's') ageHours = n / 3600; else if (u === 'm') ageHours = n / 60; else if (u === 'h') ageHours = n; else if (u === 'd') ageHours = n * 24; else if (u === 'w') ageHours = n * 168; } else if (/^\\d+\\/\\d+\\/\\d+$/.test(timeStr)) { ageHours = 72; } const contentLines = lines.slice(contentStart); const numbers = contentLines.filter(l => /^\\d+$/.test(l)); const likes = numbers.length > 0 ? parseInt(numbers[0]) : 0; const replies = numbers.length > 1 ? parseInt(numbers[1]) : 0; const textLines = contentLines.filter(l => !/^\\d+$/.test(l)); const text = textLines.join(' ').slice(0, 200); const textLower = text.toLowerCase(); if (noiseKw.some(kw => textLower.includes(kw))) return; if (textLines.join('').replace(/\\s/g, '').length < 30) return; var isReply = lines.some(function(l) { return l.trim().startsWith('Replying to'); }); if (isReply) return; if (likes === 0 && replies === 0) return; if (ageHours > 4 && likes === 0) return; var imgs = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll('img')).filter(img => img.getBoundingClientRect().width > 100); var hasMedia = imgs.length > 0 || container.querySelectorAll('video').length > 0; var isMemeLikely = hasMedia && text.length < 80; posts.push({ author, postId, url: link.href, text, likes, replies, bio, ageHours, hasMedia, isMemeLikely }); }); return posts; }"}
ENDJSON
```

