## S 4a. Duplicate Check + Post Text (combined, on post page)

After navigating to post. Combines 3s wait + DOM duplicate check + post text read into ONE evaluate:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const alreadyCommented = document.querySelectorAll('a[href*=\"/@{{handle_slug}}\"]').length > 1; const links = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a[href*=\"/post/\"]')); if (!links[0]) return { alreadyCommented, text: 'no post' }; let container = links[0]; for (let i = 0; i < 9; i++) container = container.parentElement; const lines = container ? container.innerText.split(String.fromCharCode(10)).filter(l => l.trim()) : []; const text = lines.slice(2).filter(l => !/^\\d+$/.test(l)).join(' ').slice(0, 400); return { alreadyCommented, text }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `alreadyCommented: true` → backfill to `memory/commented_posts.txt`, skip to next candidate.

## S 4b. Click Reply Button (for post pages)

Use when commenting on posts (NOT for replies from activity page).

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const icons = document.querySelectorAll('svg[aria-label=\"Reply\"]'); if (!icons[0]) return { error: 'no_reply_button' }; let el = icons[0]; while (el && el !== document.body) { if (el.getAttribute && el.getAttribute('role') == 'button') { el.click(); return { clicked: true }; } el = el.parentElement; } return { error: 'button_not_found' }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

After clicking, the 1.5s wait is embedded in S 5 (Reply/Comment Flow).

