## S 6. Click Quote

🚨 **Verified 2026-03-26:** Repost → Quote is ONE evaluate (not two). Splitting into two calls causes the menu to close before Step 2 runs (5-8s LLM overhead between calls).
🚨 **Menu items use `[role="menuitem"]`**, NOT `div[role="button"]`.

**Step 1:** Click repost icon → wait 1.5s → click Quote menuitem (ONE evaluate):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); const repostSvg = document.querySelector('svg[aria-label*=\"Repost\"]'); if (!repostSvg) return { error: 'no repost svg' }; const btn = repostSvg.closest('div[role=\"button\"]'); if (!btn) return { error: 'no repost button' }; btn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const menuItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role=\"menuitem\"]')); const quoteItem = menuItems.find(m => m.innerText.trim() === 'Quote'); if (!quoteItem) return { repostClicked: true, error: 'no Quote menuitem', items: menuItems.map(m => m.innerText.trim()) }; quoteItem.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); const dialog = document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"]'); const textbox = dialog ? dialog.querySelector('[role=\"textbox\"]') : null; return { repostClicked: true, quoteClicked: true, dialogReady: !!textbox }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `dialogReady: true` → proceed to Step 2.
If `error: 'no Quote menuitem'` → retry once (click repost again). If still fails → skip, log error.

**Step 2:** Use BROWSER-core.md S 5 (Reply/Comment Flow — has 1.5s embedded wait + type + submit in ONE evaluate).

