## S 7. Follow User (from post page — no navigation needed)

🚨 **MANDATORY before every comment and quote.** Every engagement = follow. No limit. No profile navigation.
🚨 **Verified 2026-03-28:** Post pages have a small "+" icon (`svg[aria-label="Follow"]`) next to the author's avatar. Clicking it opens a popup with a "Follow" button. After following, the icon changes to `svg[aria-label="Following"]`.

**ONE evaluate — check icon, click if needed, follow from popup:**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var svgs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('svg[aria-label=\"Follow\"], svg[aria-label=\"Following\"]')).filter(s => s.getBoundingClientRect().y > 0); var topSvg = svgs.reduce((best, s) => { var y = s.getBoundingClientRect().y; return (!best || y < best.getBoundingClientRect().y) ? s : best; }, null); if (!topSvg) return { alreadyFollowing: true }; if (topSvg.getAttribute('aria-label') === 'Following') return { alreadyFollowing: true }; var btn = topSvg.closest('div[role=\"button\"]') || topSvg.parentElement; btn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var buttons = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"button\"]')); var followBtn = buttons.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Follow' && b.getBoundingClientRect().width > 100); if (!followBtn) return { popupOpened: true, error: 'no Follow button in popup' }; followBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); document.dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent('keydown', { key: 'Escape', bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); return { followed: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `alreadyFollowing`: skip silently. If `error`: skip follow, proceed with comment (don't block engagement).

